        <updateDate>2021-05-17T18:31:25Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p>This bill prohibits the use of federal funds to implement or enforce mandates that require individuals to wear face coverings or receive vaccinations to prevent the spread of COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019).</p> <p>The bill provides for an exception that applies in health care settings.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To prohibit the use of Federal funds to propose, establish, implement, or enforce any requirement that an individual wear a mask or other face covering, or be vaccinated, to prevent the spread of COVID-19, and for other purposes.</title>
